Handmade Painting of Guru Gobind Singh Ji in Machhiwara jungle.

Waheguru ji ka khalsa Waheguru ji Ki Fateh🙏🏼

With Guru’s Blessings , I have started painting again after almost 15 years. This coming year, I’m aiming to create more art.

Machhiwara is now a small town in Ludhiana district. Guru Sahib arrived here after leaving Chamkaur on the night of 7 December 1705. Guru Sahib stopped first to rest in a garden outside the village. Here Bhai Mani Singh, Bhai Daya Singh and Bhai Dharam Singh, rejoined Guru Sahib.
May the only one “AKALPURAKH” bless us all🙏🏼

Inspired by “an unknown artist”.

Hey Akalpurakh, For all the times, I have been away from you, i was nothing but dust; lost and infused in darkness. Please enlighten my path and guide me through the journey of finally finding you🙏🏼. 
Looking forward to the #2023. 
Happy New year everyone. May the almighty Akalpurakh bless everyone 🙏🏼

‘’It is a sin to kill a Mockingbird. Mockingbirds don’t do one thing but make music for us to enjoy and sing their hearts out for us.”

“Waheguru ji ka Khalsa Waheguru ji Ki Fateh”

To kill a Mockingbird, was suggested by a loved one.As soon as the above mentioned dialogue hit! I bursted into tears. I just finished it and got so attached to the characters that I didn’t want it to be over. Such a lovely book! 
All I would say is that “A mockingbird died and is soon to be reborn.” 

#tokillamockingbird #tokillamockingbirdquotes #booktok #booklover #bookreview #bestbooks #booksthatinspire  #love #peace #one #khalsa

Waheguru ji ka khalsa, Waheguru ji Ki Fateh.

A must read! Such a beautiful book. It awakens your spiritual mind and helps you to start your spiritual journey.❣️
This book talks about the basic idea of living and creating a peaceful life around you. It explains how a single human being can either create a beautiful world or destroy it. Each and every chapter of this book is so good and worth mentioning, that I can’t write everything here. I would rather just really recommend it.

Love

Love
